18 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code Title 20, Chapter 9, Subchapter 1, is amended
19 to add an additional section to read as follows:
20 20-9-106. Ban on conversion therapy.
21 (a) As used in this section:
22 (1)(A) "Conversion therapy" means any practice or treatment
23 administered to a person that seeks to change the person's sexual orientation
24 or gender identity, including without limitation efforts to change behaviors
25 or gender expressions or to eliminate or reduce sexual or romantic
26 attractions or feelings toward persons of the same gender.
27 (B) "Conversion therapy" does not include counseling that
28 does not seek to change a person's sexual orientation or gender identity and:
29 (i) Assists a person undergoing a gender transition;
30 (ii) Provides acceptance, support, and understanding
31 to a person; or
32 (iii) Facilitates a person's coping, social support,
33 or identity exploration and development, including sexual orientation-neutral
34 intervention to prevent or address unlawful conduct or unsafe sexual
35 practices; and
36 (2) "Healthcare professional" means a person who is licensed,
